"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The replace() method is called without the inplace parameter set to True, which means it returns a new DataFrame with the replacements made, but does not modify the original DataFrame. To apply the changes to df, the result of the replace() method needs to be assigned back to df or the inplace parameter should be set to True.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< df['l2'].replace(to_replace=r'^\\u001d+$', value=0, regex=True)\\n---\\n> df['l2'].replace(to_replace=r'^\\u001d+$', value=0, regex=True, inplace=True)\"\n}"